    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy,<lb/>Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1896</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 6th ultimo,
                    suggesting that a record be kept by the masters of British sealing vessels of
                    all female nursing seals killed in Bering Sea during the coming season, I have
                    the honor to inform you that I have received a communication from Her Majesty’s
                    Government stating that they are in correspondence with the Government of Canada
                    on the subject of this proposal.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
